# Allowed signers for ChartPDS holdout "bless" commits.
#
# Any commit that touches a protected holdout path (holdout/**, holdout.lock,
# this file, or .github/workflows/holdout.yml) must be SSH-signed by a key
# listed below, or the Holdout CI check fails. This is what makes the holdout
# suite tamper-resistant against a coding agent: the agent cannot produce a
# signature from a Secure-Enclave / Touch-ID-gated key.
#
# Format (one signer per line):
#   <committer-email> namespaces="git" <key-type> <public-key>
#
# One-time setup (see docs/superpowers/specs/2026-06-27-holdout-regression-suite-design.md):
#   1. Create a Secure-Enclave SSH signing key gated by Touch ID, e.g. via
#      `secretive`, or `ssh-keygen -t ecdsa-sk` with a hardware authenticator.
#   2. Configure git to sign with it:
#        git config gpg.format ssh
#        git config user.signingkey <path-or-"key::..."-to-public-key>
#   3. Replace the placeholder line below with that public key.
#   4. Register the same public key as a *signing* key on your GitHub account
#      (Settings -> SSH and GPG keys -> New SSH key -> Key type: Signing Key)
#      so GitHub shows blessed commits as "Verified".
#
